  "text": "We addressed whether the increased CD8 + T cell accumulation noted in ProHA × TRAMP mice vaccinated in the presence of LAG-3-blocking antibody was specific for the prostate, where HA is expressed. As expected, CD8 + T cells activated by vaccination showed slightly increased trafficking to non-antigen expressing organs ( Figure 2F ). However, LAG-3 blockade did not result in further increased accumulation of clonotypic CD8 + T cells in the liver, lungs, or spleen ( Figure 2F ), organs that do not express HA in the ProHA × TRAMP mice [CITATION_1] . Accumulation of HA-specific clone 4 CD8 + cells only occurred in HA-bearing prostates ( Figure 2F ). These data show that combining LAG-3 blockade with vaccination does not result in nonspecific accumulation of clonotypic CD8 + T cells; rather, CD8 + T cells accumulate at sites of antigen expression.",
